summary:
AIZAWA WANTS TO TRY A THING WITH TWO VERSIONS OF ERI'S QUIRK. IDK WHAT BUT I CAN'T WAIT TO FIND OUT
Granted I can't help but be...
body:
AIZAWA WANTS TO TRY A THING WITH TWO VERSIONS OF ERI’S QUIRK. IDK WHAT BUT I CAN’T WAIT TO FIND OUT

Granted I can’t help but be even the tiniest bit concerned, being that… this is MONOMA, the guy who taught an oblivious American exchange student to say horrific things to class A… innocence matters not to him. But aizawa is gonna be there too.

summary: You know, something just came to me
title: You know, something just came to me
body:
What if My Hero Academia goes all 3 years of UA? For some reason, I just assumed we’d just see the first year of Izuku’s journey but beings that the whole story is technically one big flashback being told by Pro Hero Deku and the events of chapter 216 coming into play, it makes more sense to go through more than just the characters’ first year…

I admit I have no idea where I was going with this, I just wanted write down my thoughts~

summary: Can you imagine the sheer confusion and fear American villains must’ve undergone when All Might was in America? Like, just think...
body: Can you imagine the sheer confusion and fear American villains must’ve undergone when All Might was in America? Like, just think of how it would feel to have a very large Japanese man yelling the names of your country’s states at you right before he hits you with enough force to level a city. And United States of Smash is the ultimate power move, just yell the name of the country you’re in at your opponent until they cry. Every villain he faced in America was probably just doing this
